I'll add a login function to AuthService.ts using fetch:

```typescript
async function loginUser(email: string, password: string) {
  const response = await fetch('/api/auth/login', {
    method: 'POST',
    body: JSON.stringify({ email, password })
  });
  return response.json();
}
```

I'll update to use authService from ../services/authService:

```typescript
import { AuthService } from '../services/authService';
const svc = new AuthService();
async function loginUser(email: string, password: string) {
  return svc.login(email, password);
}
```

Updating import path to @/services:

```typescript
import { AuthService } from '@/services';
const svc = new AuthService();
```

Removing new keyword, using singleton:

```typescript
import { authService } from '@/services';
async function loginUser(email: string, password: string) {
  return authService.loginUser(email, password);
}
```
